# ==============================================================================
# AI Research Agent — Environment Variables Template
# IBM SkillsBuild · AICTE Internship Project
#
# HOW TO USE
# ----------
# 1. Copy this file to a NEW file named exactly:  .env
#    (the dot-prefix hides it from directory listings on Unix/macOS)
# 2. Replace each placeholder value with your real credentials.
# 3. Never commit .env to version control — it is listed in .gitignore.
#
# WHERE TO FIND THESE VALUES
# --------------------------
# IBM_API_KEY
#   IBM Cloud console → Manage → Access (IAM) → API keys → Create
#   https://cloud.ibm.com/iam/apikeys
#
# IBM_PROJECT_ID
#   IBM watsonx.ai → Projects → your project → Manage → General
#   The Project ID is a UUID shown on that page.
#   https://dataplatform.cloud.ibm.com
#
# IBM_URL
#   Use the endpoint for the region where your watsonx.ai instance lives:
#     US South  → https://us-south.ml.cloud.ibm.com   (most common)
#     EU DE     → https://eu-de.ml.cloud.ibm.com
#     EU GB     → https://eu-gb.ml.cloud.ibm.com
#     JP TOK    → https://jp-tok.ml.cloud.ibm.com
#     AU SYD    → https://au-syd.ml.cloud.ibm.com
#
# TROUBLESHOOTING: 403 no_associated_service_instance_error
# ----------------------------------------------------------
# IBM Cloud Lite and IBM SkillsBuild accounts share the WML runtime through
# the watsonx.ai platform rather than a separately-provisioned WML service
# instance.  The SDK's default initialisation path makes a pre-flight check
# that this separate instance exists, which fails on Lite accounts.
# This application resolves it by constructing APIClient(scope_validation=False)
# — see utils/ibm_client.py for details.  No changes to your IBM Cloud account
# or project configuration are required.
# ==============================================================================

IBM_API_KEY=your-ibm-cloud-api-key-here
IBM_PROJECT_ID=your-watsonx-project-id-here
IBM_URL=https://us-south.ml.cloud.ibm.com
